ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v281.group

Class OMG_O19_ORDER

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v281.group.OMG_O19_ORDER
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class OMG_O19_ORDER
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a OMG_O19_ORDER group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: ORC (Common Order)
    • 2: PRT (Participation Information) optional repeating
    • 3: OMG_O19_TIMING (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 4: OBR (Observation Request)
    • 5: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating
    • 6: PRT (Participation Information) optional repeating
    • 7: CTD (Contact Data) optional
    • 8: DG1 (Diagnosis) optional repeating
    • 9: OMG_O19_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 10: OMG_O19_SPECIMEN (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 11: OMG_O19_PRIOR_RESULT (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 12: FT1 (Financial Transaction) optional repeating
    • 13: CTI (Clinical Trial Identification) optional repeating
    • 14: BLG (Billing) optional
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
